<h1>Problem 2028 - 2024 USA TSTST, P8 of 9, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(ABC\) be a scalene triangle, and let \(D\) be a point on side \(BC\) satisfying \(\angle BAD=\angle DAC\). Suppose that \(X\) and \(Y\) are points inside \(ABC\) such that triangles \(ABX\) and \(ACY\) are similar and quadrilaterals \(ACDX\) and \(ABDY\) are cyclic. Let lines \(BX\) and \(CY\) meet at \(S\) and lines \(BY\) and \(CX\) meet at \(T\). Prove that lines \(DS\) and \(AT\) are parallel.</p>
